memgraph-full is a metapackage. It contains no files of its own; installing
it pulls in `memgraph` and `memgraph-debuginfo` at matching versions in one
step, equivalent to:

    apt install memgraph memgraph-debuginfo      # Debian/Ubuntu
    dnf install memgraph memgraph-debuginfo      # RPM-based distros

Use this when you want symbolicated stack traces and gdb-ready debug info
alongside the database, without having to remember the companion package
name.

Removal note: `apt remove memgraph-full` does not by itself uninstall
`memgraph` or `memgraph-debuginfo`, but those packages are flagged as
automatically installed. They will be removed by the next `apt autoremove`
unless you mark them manual:

    apt-mark manual memgraph memgraph-debuginfo
